Install Pip
===========

$ git clone https://github.com/pypa/pip.git
$ cd pip
$ sudo python setup.py install

Install Flask
=============

$ sudo pip install flask

In order to know where flask was installed, run the following command line:

$ pip show flask


$ python hello.py
http://0.0.0.0:5000

Visit that URL in your favorite browser and you should see "Hello!".

You can also avoid having to type 'python' everytime by doing:

$ chmod +x ./hello.py
$ ./hello.py


Install Gunicorn
================

$ sudo pip install gunicorn

$ gunicorn -b 0.0.0.0:8000 hello:app
